            <a id="btnMissCallAnchorTag" class="btn btn-green font24 buyer-call-btn" data-role="click-tracking" data-event="CWInteractive" data-action="MissCall_clicked" data-cat="Insurance OTP_lead drop_d" data-label="MissCall_clicked" >
                <span class="fa fa-phone margin-right10 position-rel pos-top3">
                </span><span id="btnMissCall" class="font18"></span>
            </a>
            <img id="imgLoadingBtnMissCall" src="https://imgd.aeplcdn.com/0x0/statics/loader.gif" class="position-rel pos-top5 pos-left5 hide" width="16" height="16">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<!-- otp popup code end -->

<section class="container">
    <div class="grid-12">
        <h2 class="text-center margin-top50 margin-bottom30 special-skin-text">FAQs</h2>

        <div class="content-box-shadow content-inner-block-10 margin-bottom20">

            <p class="font16 text-default-color text-bold margin-top5">What is car insurance?</p>
            <p class="font14 text-default-color margin-top10 margin-bottom30">
                Car insurance provides protection to the car's owner against third-party liabilities, theft or damage to the car. It also provides cover against
                accidental injuries. There are two types of car insurance. 1. Third Party only. 2. Comprehensive or Package policy.
            </p>

            <p class="font16 text-default-color text-bold">Is insurance mandatory to have?</p>
            <p class="font14 text-default-color margin-top10 margin-bottom30">
                As per law, it's mandatory to have third-party insurance for your car. Opting for a comprehensive policy is a matter of choice. CarWale
                recommends you a comprehensive policy, though.
            </p>

            <p class="font16 text-default-color text-bold">Benefits of comprehensive car insurance?</p>
            <p class="font14 text-default-color margin-top10 margin-bottom30">
                Comprehensive car insurance not only protects you against third party liabilities but also helps you avoid unnecessary expenses that might occur
                due to accidents or theft.
            </p>

            <p class="font16 text-default-color text-bold">What is No Claim Bonus (NCB)?</p>
            <p class="font14 text-default-color margin-top10 margin-bottom15">
                It is a benefit offered by the insurer to those who have not claimed insurance during the previous year of cover. It means that the next premium
                amount to be paid would be lower.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clear"></div>
</section>
